<HEADLINE> Aguilera Cancels Syracuse Show  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SYRACUSE, N.Y. (AP) -- Christina Aguilera isn't coming back -- at
least for now.
</P>
<P>
   The pop star, whose Sept. 3 concert at the New York State Fair
was called off due to laryngitis, can't reschedule another show
into her busy concert plans, promoters said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   ''We deeply regret that a rescheduled show couldn't be fit into
her remaining East coast schedule,'' Ron Baird of the booking
agency Creative Artists Agency said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
   Fair spokesman Joe LaGuardia said all of the nearly 12,000
tickets that had been sold for the show would be refunded at
purchase points.
</P>
<P>
   Aguilera sings pop hits including ''Genie In A Bottle'' and ''I
Turn To You.'' She is scheduled to perform Thursday at MTV's video
music awards in New York City.
</P>
