<HEADLINE> US to Indonesia: Disarm Militias  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   UNITED NATIONS (AP) -- After the killing of three U.N. workers in
West Timor, President Clinton called on Indonesia Thursday to
disarm the militias and ''bring those responsible to justice.''
</P>
<P>
   Clinton opened an address to the Security Council by taking note
of deaths of the three U.N. workers Wednesday at the hands of a mob
led by pro-Indonesian militia gangs at the border town of Atambua.
</P>
