<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Survey: Confident Connecticut companies tapping into the Net  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   HARTFORD, Conn. (AP) - The majority of the state's small to
mid-size businesses are taking advantage of the Internet to grow
their companies, according to a statewide survey released Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   The survey, conducted by the Connecticut Business and Industry
Association, also indicated a high level of confidence from
companies doing business in the state.
</P>
<P>
   Of the 816 business executives surveyed in May and June, 54
percent said their companies have a Web site and 15 percent more
are planning to launch a site next year. That contrasts sharply
with the 1997 survey, when 28 percent of those surveyed had a
company Web site.
</P>
<P>
   Confidence in Connecticut as a place to do business also has
increased, reaching 72 percent this year, up 4 percentage points
from last year. In 1994, when CBIA started the survey, only 42
percent of companies surveyed expressed confidence.
</P>
<P>
   The lending climate also drew a favorable response. More than
half the respondents said it was good, while 39 percent found it
fair. Ten percent thought the lending climate was poor.
</P>
<P>
   ''Despite all this good news about our state, we do still have
our share of challenges,'' said Pierre Guertin, a partner in the
Hartford office of consulting firm Arthur Andersen. Among the
concerns are a worker shortage, an anticipated slowdown in the U.S.
economy and business costs.
</P>
<P>
   Nearly 31 percent of respondents indicated labor costs were
their biggest worry. Health care costs were the top concern for 12
percent of those surveyed.
</P>
<P>
   Transportation also is a challenge in the state. Some 64 percent
said a first-rate transportation infrastructure is important to
Connecticut's overall economic growth.
</P>
<P>
   The survey was mailed to 5,000 small and midsize businesses in
May and June and 816 were returned, a response rate of 16 percent.
The margin of error was 3.5 percentage points.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
