	   BERLIN, N.J. (AP) - The FBI on Thursday was looking for a
suspect who robbed a Berlin bank after giving a teller a note
demanding money, an official said.
</P>
<P>
   The man, wearing a brown plaid jacket, entered the Commerce Bank
at 247 S. White Horse Pike at about 1:30 p.m. and presented a
teller with a note demanding money, said FBI Special Agent Linda
Vizi, of the bureau's Cherry Hill office.
</P>
