<DOCNO> APW20000907.0148 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-07 19:11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canadiens Sign Zubrus  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MONTREAL (AP) -- Right wing Dainius Zubrus signed a two-year, $2
million contract with the Montreal Canadiens on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Zubrus, 22, of Lithuania, had 14 goals and 28 assists in 73
games last season. He joined the Canadiens in March 1999 trade that
sent Mark Recchi to Philadelphia.
</P>
<P>
   ''The expectations are there and I have no problem with that,''
Zubrus said. ''I'm just happy that I don't have to worry about
contracts any more.
</P>
<P>
   ''There's a lot of things I thought about that I can do to my
game. The whole teams looks good now. I hope we all chip in and
make the playoffs.''
</P>
</TEXT>
