<HEADLINE> Sabres Extend Woolley's Contract  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BUFFALO, N.Y. (AP) -- Jason Woolley, who led Buffalo Sabres'
defensemen in scoring last season, agreed to a multiyear contract
extension Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Terms of the deal were not released.
</P>
<P>
   Woolley, an assistant captain last season, had previously been
under contract for one year after accepting the team's $1.045
million qualifying offer last July.
</P>
