<HEADLINE> Blue Jays' Mondesi Will Try Again  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   TORONTO (AP) -- Toronto Blue Jays outfielder Raul Mondesi, who
had surgery on his right elbow on Aug. 14, will try to play again
this season.
</P>
<P>
   Mondesi, eligible to come off the 60-day disabled list on Sept.
20, threw for the first time in five weeks. He will take batting
practice on Friday.
</P>
<P>
   ''I feel good,'' Mondesi, who had 14 bone chips removed from his
elbow, said Thursday. ''I'll see how I feel, and how the team does
in the next couple of weeks. If we're in contention for the
playoffs I'll try to come back.''
</P>
<P>
   The Blue Jays began the day 4&AMP;frac12; games behind Cleveland in the
wild card race.
</P>
<P>
   Mondesi said he would also consider playing if the Blue Jays are
out of contention.
</P>
<P>
   ''It depends on what the trainers, the manager and the owner
says,'' Mondesi said.
</P>
<P>
   Mondesi, acquired from Los Angeles in the offseason, hit .272
with 24 homers and 67 RBIs in 95 games.
</P>
<P>
   He'd been away from the team for a few weeks, but when he walked
onto the field before the game, his teammates gave him a loud
ovation
</P>
<P>
   ''He's a presence in the clubhouse,'' Toronto manager Jim
Fregosi said. ''He plays with such abandonment. He's an integral
part of our offense and defense.''
</P>
</TEXT>
