<HEADLINE> ACC, SEC Form Officiating Program  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   GREENSBORO, N.C. (AP) -- The Atlantic Coast Conference and the
Southeastern Conference have formed an officiating program to
assign referees for regular-season and postseason tournament men's
basketball games starting with the 2000-01 season.
</P>
<P>
   The ACC/SEC Regional Officiating Program, announced Thursday,
will be based in Atlanta. John Guthrie, who previously coordinated
men's basketball officiating for the SEC, will head the program.
Fred Barakat, who previously coordinated ACC men's basketball
officiating, will serve as a liaison and help establish the
program.
</P>
<P>
   ACC commissioner John Swofford said the move will provide a
larger pool of officials for both leagues.
</P>
</TEXT>
