<HEADLINE> Tennessee's Mathews Hurts Knee  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   KNOXVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Tennessee quarterback Joey Mathews left
practice early Thursday because of a knee injury, and is scheduled
to have an MRI exam Friday.
</P>
<P>
   ''He just kind of felt it pop,'' Vols coach Phillip Fulmer said.
''It's obviously a concern to us. He said he didn't know when he
did it or if he did it.''
</P>
<P>
   Mathews practiced Tuesday and Wednesday, leaving each day with
an ice bag wrapped around his left knee.
</P>
<P>
   The No. 12 Volunteers are idle this weekend. They will face No.
8 Florida next Saturday.
