<HEADLINE> Obituaries in the News  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated PressDavid M. Haskell:
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Actor David M. Haskell, who starred in stage
and film versions of ''Godspell'' as well as the role of Nick
Hartley on the soap opera ''Santa Barbara,'' died Aug. 30 of brain
cancer. He was 52.
</P>
<P>
   In addition to the modernized version of the story of Jesus
Christ in ''Godspell'' in the 1970s, Haskell's stage credits
included a production of Shakespeare's ''Measure for Measure''
opposite Meryl Streep.
</P>
<P>
   Haskell's film credits include ''Seems Like Old Times,'' ''Deal
of the Century,'' ''Body Double'' and ''The Boost.'' He also
appeared in television movie and miniseries productions, including
''Missing Pieces,'' ''Policewoman Centerfold,'' ''Princess Daisy''
and ''Mickey Spillane's Mike Hammer: More Than Murder.''
William A. Hudson:
</P>
<P>
   LOUISVILLE, Ky. (AP) -- William A. ''Bill'' Hudson, a retired
Kentucky broadcast editor for The Associated Press, died Wednesday.
He was 79.
</P>
<P>
   Hudson started with the AP on Feb. 6, 1944 and retired Feb. 1,
1984.
</P>
<P>
   Hudson covered University of Kentucky football and basketball
while Lexington correspondent early in his 40-year career with the
wire service.
</P>
<P>
   In later years, he served as broadcast editor in the AP's
Louisville bureau.
</P>
<P>
   He was a former member of the Kentucky Press Association and the
Kentucky Broadcasters Association.
</P>
<P>
   Hudson is survived by his wife, a son, two daughters, five
grandchildren and three great grandchildren.
</P>
</TEXT>
